Something that you're well versed in and probably 
address is the impact of urban renewal in Austin

28:02.232 --> 28:20.169
and what role the city has played as far as having 
people write grants and use available federal

28:02.232 --> 28:20.169
funding as a resource for stimulating local 
development. Could you say something about that?

28:23.292 --> 28:26.776
Austin was extremely active in the urban renewal 
programs. It had five urban renewal, very

28:26.796 --> 28:31.480
significant urban renewal projects. Today there 
are two of which have not yet totally been

28:32.776 --> 28:36.861
completed. It was a major development activity 
that led to the expansion of the Capitol Complex.

28:44.611 --> 28:48.676
It was a major development activity that led to the 
expansion of the University of Texas. It was a

28:50.098 --> 28:56.165
major development activity that led to the 
beautification and saving of Waller Creek. And

28:57.507 --> 28:58.969
then in East Austin, There are three areas in which 
it had a tremendous impact on the removal of slums

28:59.135 --> 29:07.046
and blight and replatting in the typical sense. 
But there are some unique factors in the Austin

29:08.448 --> 29:14.517
Urban Renewal Program that are not generally 
known even by Austinites. Among those, the LBJ

29:15.839 --> 29:20.606
Library is located on urban renewal land. The 
expansion of the university, the Super Drum,

29:20.646 --> 29:27.015
Brackenridge Hospital, all of those lands were 
made available through the use of the urban

29:27.805 --> 29:34.594
renewal power, which is very, very significant. 
It has recently come to light that there have been

29:34.614 --> 29:41.945
problems with accountability of funding that 
Austin has received from the federal government.

29:44.728 --> 29:49.355
What do you see as the prospect for urban renewal 
and federal funding in Austin City? As a result of

29:49.555 --> 29:54.522
that, how has planning been affected by the 
problems that Austin has had recently? Well, the

29:55.970 --> 30:08.568
Urban Renewal Program, of course, expired in 
1974, so the possibility of a rebirth of urban

29:55.970 --> 30:08.568
renewal is remote unless new federal legislation 
is prepared. Funding problems today result in the

30:10.591 --> 30:14.777
Community Development Program. The lack of 
funding currently, it's not been a long period,

30:15.659 --> 30:24.171
four or five months without funding, have 
resulted in the impairment of rehabilitation

30:24.539 --> 30:30.409
programs to assist neighborhoods in keeping 
those neighborhoods viable living

30:24.539 --> 30:30.409
environments. They've had some effect on 
planning, but not very much. The planning

30:34.857 --> 30:44.013
function in the city of Austin has been 
self-sufficient and supported by the city itself

30:34.857 --> 30:44.013
and has never really depended heavily on federal 
funds for its operation. As far as projects that

30:47.827 --> 30:50.951
planners have envisioned for Austin that have 
been affected by this? What kind of

30:50.991 --> 30:58.462
accommodations are being made to adjust goals and 
timeframes?

30:58.482 --> 31:05.251
Well, you're talking about the cut off the funds or 
the... There don't appear to be any

31:05.271 --> 31:11.460
adjustments to be made, really. The majority of 
the funds that have been cut off affect housing

31:12.160 --> 31:17.648
rehabilitation, which is an ongoing, forever 
problem. There have not been, because of the

31:18.775 --> 31:26.787
restrictive use of the funds, any great new 
community-wide type projects that were planned

31:18.775 --> 31:26.787
using these funds. So it's not had an effect on 
those. The funds are restricted in their use

31:28.990 --> 31:32.074
anyway. There has been ongoing planning, 
continues to be, for I think the convention

31:32.094 --> 31:37.862
center. There's been discussions of a new city 
hall. There's ongoing development on Town Lake.

31:44.232 --> 31:48.698
All of that's privately and publicly supported, 
apart from any federal funding. But there is a

31:49.437 --> 32:00.308
significant impact when you consider that five or 
six months of rehabilitation activity has had to

31:49.437 --> 32:00.308
stop, and that affects hundreds of families.

